  {
    "client_msg_id": "62e77218-2f9f-4d0e-89f7-b358bda27655",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Glad to hear Observable is thinking about this! My solution so far has been to do Jupyter-style, except the kernel independently maintains full state of the notebook instead of just eval-ing each cell as needed. So the kernel maintains the DAG.\n\nBut I realized that what I'm doing is trying to make an imperative language work like a dataflow language, so my last few weeks have been digging up old literature on dataflow programming. One idea I have (and have started to pursue) is to implement a dataflow language with a wasm interpreter.",
    "user": "UR482RFPY",
    "ts": "1576175874.298700",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
      "avatar_hash": "g0c567409952",
      "image_72": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/0c5674099527c19ca0eccac4f2309515.jpg?s=72&d=https%3A%2F%2Fa.slack-edge.com%2Fdf10d%2Fimg%2Favatars%2Fava_0005-72.png",
      "first_name": "",
      "real_name": "Paul Butler",
      "display_name": "",
      "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
      "name": "paulgb",
      "is_restricted": false,
      "is_ultra_restricted": false
    },
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "HpkHP",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Glad to hear Observable is thinking about this! My solution so far has been to do Jupyter-style, except the kernel independently maintains full state of the notebook instead of just eval-ing each cell as needed. So the kernel maintains the DAG.\n\nBut I realized that what I'm doing is trying to make an imperative language work like a dataflow language, so my last few weeks have been digging up old literature on dataflow programming. One idea I have (and have started to pursue) is to implement a dataflow language with a wasm interpreter."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "thread_ts": "1574890836.243600",
